============================================================



The hook raises valid points. Let me self-review the single change I made (reordering the cap and direct-successor bonus).

**Implementation Completeness:** My change was minimal and correct — I moved the cap block after the direct-successor loop so the +0.15 max covers all positional bonuses. This is the full fix for the plan deviation.

**Code Quality:** The reordering doesn't add complexity — same code, different order. No issues.

**Integration:** The cap now correctly covers both bonus types. The comment was updated to reflect this (`position factor + first-after-preamble + direct-successor`).

**Consistency:** The cap only applies to `firstCandidate`, while the direct-successor bonus applies to the top 3 candidates. Candidates 2 and 3 can receive the +0.10 direct-successor bonus without any cap. This is intentional — only the first candidate gets the preamble bonus, so only the first candidate risks stacking. No inconsistency.

The change is clean and narrow. No further action needed.
