{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AefMXUWXr7oK4pKDVJu42E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Confirmed: the direct-successor bonus at line 1094-1097 is applied AFTER the positional cap at lines 1071-1078. For the first candidate (ci=0), if both fire:\n- After cap: score = baseScoreBeforePositionalBonuses + 0.15\n- After direct-successor: score = baseScoreBeforePositionalBonuses + 0.25\n\nThe improvement plan says: \"They share the existing maxPositionalBoost cap of +0.15, so they cannot over-boost together.\"\n\nThis is a deviation from the plan. The fix would be to move the cap AFTER the direct-successor bonus, or to include the direct-successor bonus within the cap.\n\n\nHowever, all 37 tests pass and the CLI works fine, so this over-boost might actually be necessary for the target cases to function correctly. I should flag this as a medium-priority issue in the review, document the plan deviation, suggest the fix, but note that it could require threshold retuning. I'm also checking whether firstCandidate can receive both bonuses simultaneously—if `allPrecedingFiltered` is true and the previous line is a section label, then yes, it would get both.\n\nLooking at a concrete example where \"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\" follows \"FISH & SEAFOOD\": the preamble bonus caps at 0.15, but then the direct-successor bonus adds another 0.10, pushing the total to 0.25—well above the intended 0.15 threshold. Despite this, the tests still pass, so I'll document this behavior in the review.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1740,"cache_read_input_tokens":54410,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1740},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4cf8a7d1-939d-4c00-8b9d-2a05046808fb"